        "id": 2874500,
        "name": "Andrew Northup",
        "username": "AD_Northup",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/ad_northup/{size}/2940_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-04-24T21:06:30.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Went in Search of this wine after a combination of reading Robert Walters\u2019s book and watching WIlliam Kelley\u2019s Instagram Live session on Bouchard. This is instantly my wine of the year by a mile, based on my personal tastes.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=3263525&amp;iNote=8331991\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><strong>2015 Roses de Jeanne / C\u00e9dric Bouchard Champagne Blanc de Noirs La Presle</strong></a> <em>- France, Champagne (4/24/2020)</em><br>\nColor is a very pale straw yellow, absolutely gorgeous. Pleasant nose of various fruits, some floral notes and just a hint of a savory spice I can\u2019t quite identify. Incredibly fine mousse, but very delicate on the tongue. Mouthfeel is incredibly light hitting center tongue and slowly falling over the sides. Acidity is moderate, not taking over at all. First thing on the tongue is a burst of fruits, very sweet apple, some citrus peel/rind, just the perfect amount of sweetness. As the wine rolls off the sides of your tongue, a beautiful minerality and dryness hits followed by a little creaminess, creating an amazing lingering finish along with the primary taste flavors that lasts for an incredibly long time. This is a next level champagne for me, absolutely perfect for my tastes, and even given the price tag I think I\u2019ll have to load up quite a bit. <em><strong>(98 pts.)</strong></em>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/original/3X/d/b/db8a8cd0335997803e1f95235f5c8d565ab0891d.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/db8a8cd0335997803e1f95235f5c8d565ab0891d\" title=\"\"><img src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/d/b/db8a8cd0335997803e1f95235f5c8d565ab0891d_2_375x499.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-base62-sha1=\"vk9piUuWzGSBE2Em5ILeL7bEQ8d\" role=\"presentation\" width=\"375\" height=\"499\" srcset=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/d/b/db8a8cd0335997803e1f95235f5c8d565ab0891d_2_375x499.jpeg, https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/original/3X/d/b/db8a8cd0335997803e1f95235f5c8d565ab0891d.jpeg 1.5x, https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/original/3X/d/b/db8a8cd0335997803e1f95235f5c8d565ab0891d.jpeg 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"7F7E75\"><div class=\"meta\">\n<svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\"></span><span class=\"informations\">465\u00d7620 38.9 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg>\n</div></a></div></p>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>",
